cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DC 

The paper deals with deep learning networks for computer vision workloads, specifically image classification and object detection. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses techniques for improving the performance of these networks, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of low-precision numerics and model compression, which are techniques used in artificial intelligence and neural networks, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) likely categories as well. Finally, the paper deals with the deployment of these models on resource-constrained inference systems, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing, making cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) a possible category.
